rows.label: tev068101_SEL0021
rows.name: Ask Ge Jewhe about recent developments.

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0001
rows.name:
I once battled with the Milsaadi near
the Forgotten Mining Frigates.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0002
rows.name:
Even alone, they could fell lesser opponents in a
stroke. But they were not aloneâ€”the insects at their
command attacked me relentlessly.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0003
rows.name:
They were worthy warriors indeed.
In the end, I was unable to claim victory.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0004
rows.name:
If you head that way, you should challenge them.
If nothing else, they will make you stronger![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0006
rows.name:
I intended to go out hunting, believing I might replenish
our food stores...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0007
rows.name:
But when she found out, Vi Sezha rose against me like
a thunderstorm. It took half a day to convince her to
let me go![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0008
rows.name:
I suppose my days of leaving her to do my own thing
are well done.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev068101_MSG0009
rows.name: The laws of Wroth have nothing on that one's grip.[ST:wait ]
